Add a ssd demo running on linux (#29)

* Add configurarion of ssd model and main source files.

* Add pre-commit configs.

* Support the use of OpenCV to read image.

* Create README.md

* Define class ImageRecognizer to simplify the inferfaces.

* Print more result's information.

* Reorganize the sub-directory of demo.

* Use threshold to profile the result.

* Add script file to download model.

* Add function resize_hwc to resize input image, and move the substract of means into ImageRecognizer::infer().

* Refine the code format.

* Enable the input image to rotate 0, 90, 180 and 270.

* Fix out of range crash and set memory pool size of Paddle to 0.

* Enable the transferring from BGR to RGB.

* Draw rectangles to show the results.

* Rename demo to Demo.

* Reorganize the directory.

* Reorganize the image related code.
